article.headline: U of the Pacific 62, Idaho 56
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- Miah Davis scored 18 points in Pacific's seventh straight victory, 62-56 over Idaho on Thursday night. Tyler Newton had 14 points and David Doubley added 11 as the streaking Tigers improved to 11-1 in the Big West Conference, setting up a showdown with No. 19 Utah State for the conference lead on Saturday. Pacific (16-7) never managed to take a large lead over the Vandals (9-13, 6-7), whose four-game winning streak was snapped despite 16 points and six rebounds from Tyrone Hayes. Dwayne Williams added 14 points.
